    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1984-01-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1984-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="263"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <head>263. Telegram From the Embassy in the German Democratic Republic to the
                    Department of State<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d263fn1">Source: Reagan
                        Library, Executive Secretariat, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Cable
                        File, Europe (State) NODIS IN (01/21/1984–04/23/1984). Confidential; Niact
                        Immediate; Nodis.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">261.</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>East Berlin</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1984-01-26">January 26, 1984, 1401Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <!--<pb facs="d263-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d263-2"/>-->
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <rs corresp="reccPNaD9EAQIn4zj" type="topic">Asylum</rs> Seekers in
                        Embassy.</item>
                </list>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>REF</head>
                    <item>(A) Berlin 260;<note n="2" xml:id="d263fn2">See <ref target="#d262"
                                >Document 262</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <item>(B) Berlin 255;<note n="3" xml:id="d263fn3">See <ref target="#d262fn3"
                                >footnote 3, Document 262</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <item>(C) State 23572.<note n="4" xml:id="d263fn4">See <ref target="#d262fn2"
                                >footnote 2, Document 262</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>C—Entire text.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The family of three left voluntarily at about 1430 hours after speaking
                        with EmbOff. They were not stopped immediately on departure, but a <gloss
                            target="#t_GDR_1">GDR</gloss> police car moved off after they turned the
                        corner, and we can only assume they will be at least questioned.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>The young man who came earlier (Ref B) remains in the landing area, still
                        refusing to depart. We have continued to make the case that <rs
                            corresp="reccPNaD9EAQIn4zj" type="topic">asylum</rs> is not possible and
                        that it is in his best interests to leave and pursue existing mechanisms. He
                        still maintains he has been in jail once before and has nothing to lose by
                        staying.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RR_2">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ridgway</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
